                    "text": "(Huston, 2004)",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF11"
                },
                {
                    "start": 1074,
                    "end": 1088,
                    "text": "(Huston, 2004)",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF11"
                },
                {
                    "start": 1294,
                    "end": 1307,
                    "text": "(Heard, 2004)",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF10"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Although the origin of the cardiac lesions remains uncertain, the very young age of the rabbit is suggestive of a congenital myocardial disease, which should be taken into consideration in the differential diagnosis of sudden cardiac death in rabbits. In particular, when sudden unexpected or perioperative cardiac death occurs as a result of refractory arrhythmias or asystole in rabbits, necropsy and histopathological examinations should be performed in order to confirm/exclude the presence of myocardial lesions.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        }
